  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Head Chef",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Oversee daily kitchen operations and food preparation</p></li><li><p>Plan menus and ensure quality and consistency of dishes</p></li><li><p>Manage kitchen staff schedules and workflow</p></li><li><p>Maintain hygiene, cleanliness, and safety standards</p></li><li><p>Monitor inventory and order supplies as needed</p></li><li><p>Ensure compliance with food safety regulations</p></li><li><p>Assist in training junior kitchen staff</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Requirements</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Minimum 18 years old</p></li><li><p>Prior cooking or kitchen supervision experience preferred</p></li><li><p>Strong leadership and organisational skills</p></li><li><p>Ability to work in a fast-paced environment</p></li><li><p>Basic knowledge of food safety and hygiene standards</p></li><li><p>Positive attitude and ability to manage a small team</p></li></ul><h3><strong>What We Offer</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Monthly salary between <strong>SGD 2,500 – 2,800</strong></p></li><li><p>On-the-job training provided</p></li><li><p>Opportunity to manage and grow a kitchen team</p></li><li><p>Supportive and collaborative work environment</p></li><li><p>Potential for career progression based on performance</p></li></ul><h3><strong>How to Apply</strong></h3><p>Shortlisted candidates will be contacted for a brief phone discussion, followed by a detailed walkthrough of the role and expectations.</p>",
